{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Dragon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Dragon|prevnum=705|prev=Sliggoo|nextnum=707|next=Klefki|roundleft=tl|roundright=tr}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Goodra}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Goodra\n|jname=ヌメルゴン\n|jtranslit=Numerugon\n|tmname=Numelgon\n|image=706Goodra.png\n|category=Dragon\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Dragon\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Sap Sipper\n|ability2=Hydration\n|abilityd=Gooey\n|ndex=706\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=021\n|adex=180\n|height-ftin=6\'07"\n|height-m=2.0\n|weight-lbs=331.8\n|weight-kg=150.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Dragon\n|gendercode=127\n|eggcycles=40\n|evtotal=3\n|evsd=3\n|expyield=270\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|color=Purple\n|catchrate=45\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=goodra\n|generation=6\n|friendship=35\n}}\n\'\'\'Goodra\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ヌメルゴン\'\'\' \'\'Numelgon\'\') is a {{type|Dragon}} [[pseudo-legendary Pokémon]] introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Sliggoo}} starting at level 50 when leveled up during [[rain]] or [[fog]] in the overworld. Rain instigated by {{m|Rain Dance}}, {{a|Drizzle}} or {{a|Primordial Sea}} will not trigger this evolution. It is the final form of {{p|Goomy}}.\n\n==Biology==\nGoodra is a bipedal, draconic Pokémon that is coated with slime. Most of its body is pale purple with a darker purple underside. It has bright green eyes, two green spots on each cheek, a relatively long neck, and a short, rounded snout. On top of its head are two pairs of antenna-like horns. The foremost horns are small nubs, but the hind horns are longer, thicker, and curve down its neck. The tips of the larger horns are slightly curled. It has proportionally short limbs with two digits each and a large, thick tail with a curled tip. Along each side of its tail are three green spots. A pale green slime is usually visible dripping from its chin and arms.\n\nBecause of its meek, friendly nature, Goodra is often teased. However, it will strike at its tormentors with its retractable horns and powerful tail. It is also capable of throwing punches with incredible force. Its slimy coating in combination with a layer of fat causes attacks to slide off. When it grows close to someone, it will hug them and leave them coated in slime. If it is left alone, it will ooze gooey tears.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Ash Goodra.png|left|thumb|250px|Goodra in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Ash\'s Goodra]]====\n{{Ash}}\'s Sliggoo [[Evolution|evolved]] into a Goodra in \'\'[[XY065|Good Friends, Great Training!]]\'\', using {{m|Rain Dance}} to trigger its evolution. Ash {{pkmn2|released}} it in \'\'[[XY070|Beyond the Rainbow!]]\'\', but it rejoined Ash\'s party for the [[Lumiose Conference]] in \'\'[[XY126|Valuable Experience for All!]]\'\'. It was released again in \'\'[[XY139|Facing the Needs of the Many!]]\'\'.\n\n===Minor appearances===\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY065|Goodra|Ash\'s Pokédex|Goodra, the Dragon Pokémon and the evolved form of {{p|Sliggoo}}. Goodra is very friendly, and one of its hugs can cover its Trainer with a sticky slime.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Zinnia Goodra Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Goodra in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon - The Legend of the Dragon King manga===\nA Goodra debuted in [[LDK4]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nIn \'\'[[PAORAS04|Omega Alpha Adventure 4]]\'\', a Goodra appeared as a silhouette during {{Steven}}\'s explanation about the [[Draconid people]].\n\n[[Zinnia]] used a Goodra during her raids on [[Sea Mauville]] and the [[Mossdeep Space Center]] in \'\'[[PAORAS08|Omega Alpha Adventure 8]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Goodra (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=dragon}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=021|label1=Mountain|reg2=